{
  "texts": [
    "Another interesting idea was presented by Korkmaz (2022), where they show that reward-based incentives can reveal the inherent bias of an LLM.",
    "As you may have already noticed, most works focus on limited demographics like gender or nationality.",
    "Also, these methods are not easily extendable to a broad set of stereotypes.",
    "For example, sentiment analysis does not provide a comprehensive picture of societal stereotypes and will not be able to detect the stereotype of a person from a specific country being dirty.",
    "LSI addresses these issues."
  ]
}